   "source": [
    "1. To what does a relative path refer?\n",
    "\n",
    "--> There are two ways to specify a file path: Absolute Path, Relative Path\n",
    "--> Relative Path specifies the filepath which is relative to the program's current working directory."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "63ba013b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "2. What does an absolute path start with your operating system?\n",
    "\n",
    "--> Absolute Path specifies the file path which always begins with the root folder.\n",
    "--> For a windows operating system the absolute file path starts with C:\\ and for Linux it is /."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "543c294e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
